        <p>(50) Sketch the blocks for making a ball move horizontally, back and forth, continuously. When the ball hits the right edge it should start going left, when it hits the left edge it should start going right.
        <div id="myCollapsibleExample"><a href="#demo3" data-toggle="collapse">Answer</a></div>
        <div id="demo3" class="collapse">
            <p>Following are two solutions for this question. The key is that you need to define a variable, named "distance" in the solutions below, that "remembers" whether the ball is moving left or right. So if distance is 5, the ball is moving right, if distance is -5, it is moving left. The solutions below differ in how the variable is changed when an edge is reached.</p>
